ten nach Artt. 121, 122 GEKR -- tVerpflichtungen des Käufers, Artt. 123-130 GEKR -- tDie Abhilfen des Verkäufers nach Artt. 131-139 GEKR -- tGefahrübergang nach Artt. 140 ff . GEKR -- tSchadensersatz und Zinsen nach EU-Kaufrecht -- tDie Verjährung im EU-Kaufrecht -- tBackmatter0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aAm 11.10.2011 hat die Europäische Kommission ihren "Vorschlag für eine Verordnung über ein Gemeinsames Europäisches Kaufrecht" und damit den Vorschlag für ein Optionales Instrument vorgelegt. Namhafte Autoren des europäischen Privat- und Wirtschaftsrechts analysieren in diesem topaktuellen Buch, systematisch orientiert am Aufbau der Verordnung, den Kommissionsvorschlag. Zugleich bietet der Band eine Bewertung der mit dem Vorschlag verbundenen Sachentscheidungen und technischen Lösungen. So dient Ihnen dieses wichtige Werk in der aktuellen Diskussion um das bislang spektakulärste Gesetzgebungsvorhaben im europäischen Privatrecht als unverzichtbare Grundlage für einen vertieften Einblick in die Normstruktur.  aGovernments, or at least the clever ones among them, are aware of the factors guiding business activities. In the course of adopting and enforcing economic legislation, they seek to attract business activities in order to increase national income (and fiscal revenues), generate employment opportunities and,very generally, please voters. Hence economic law may be considered an economic good, as suggested by the title of this book.That function, which most rules of economic law have in the competition of systems, was strengthened by the worldwide liberalization of trade. Today, it is of greater significance than ever before.Lawyers and economists, academics and practitioners from inside and outside Germany have taken a look at the facts and discussed approaches to conceptualizing them. The resulting thirty essays collected in this volume contribute to the interpretation of existing, and the making of new, economic law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEuropean law and economics. 0aEuropean law. 0aLawxInternational unification. 0aSaleszEuropean Union countries. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh1 aBenninghoff, Sonja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFehrenbach, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGebauer, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrädler, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKöchel, Manuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLooschelders, Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMakowsky, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartens, Sebastian A.E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaultzsch, Felix, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMöslein, Florian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller-Graff, Peter-Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRemien, Oliver, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchaub, Renate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmidt-Kessel, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmidt-Kessel, Martin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWeller, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWendehorst, Christiane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWiese, Volker, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc